                    <comment id="12382095" author="ilyak@mainsoft.com" created="Mon, 10 Jan 2005 07:55:02 +0000"  >Created an attachment (id=13960)&lt;br/&gt;
Patch for TestRedirects test case&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
Please note: since the max_redirect and allow_circular_redirects throw same&lt;br/&gt;
exceptions - RedirectException, the only way to understand real reason to&lt;br/&gt;
exception is to parse the message of exception.&lt;br/&gt;
For my opinion, circular references should throw exception of inherited from&lt;br/&gt;
RedirectException (e.g. class CircularRedirectException extends&lt;br/&gt;
RedirectException) - this will save on the backward compatibility and provide&lt;br/&gt;
better error handling.</comment>
